article.description: Tre'Von Willis scored 16 points as UNLV (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today) pulled away from Southern Utah 77-59 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Willis' 16 points lead UNLV past Southern Utah
article.linkText: Willis' 16 points lead UNLV past Southern Utah
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- Tre'Von Willis scored 16 points as UNLV (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today) pulled away from Southern Utah 77-59 Tuesday night. Chace Stanback added 15 points and Oscar Bellfield 10 as the Runnin' Rebels (8-1) bounced back from their only loss, having fallen 95-80 Saturday against Kansas State. The Rebels led 31-30 at intermission and then, up 34-32 early in the second half, went on a 20-4 run to go ahead 54-36 and put the game away. Davis Baker led all scorers with 21 points for the Thunderbirds (3-8), who lost their sixth in a row. Matt Hodgson had a game-high eight rebounds for Southern Utah. Though UNLV was outrebounded 43-38, the Rebels forced 25 turnovers while committing only 10. Southern Utah achieved its largest lead with 17:22 left in the first half when Hodgson's jump shot made it 8-2. UNLV ran its record against Southern Utah to 19-0.
